<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The intercom crackled to life, &quot;Okay, Sasha, stay calm횄짖창혗짭횂짝  Let's think logically횄짖창혗짭횂짝  Just because the Pattern Scanner is finding more and more, it could be that the 'rocks' could just be cracking up into the blood stream횄짖창혗짭횂짝  we need to study it some more.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Sasha looked to Bruce, &quot;Can we access the slides in the Electron microscope while keeping them in the Pattern Scanner?&quot;</P>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Bruce smiled, &quot;Sure횄짖창혗짭횂짝  I just patch the PS's built-in microscope into the Electron.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Bruce had a patch cable running between the two machines in minutes.  He pointed to the devices, &quot;You can control the slide shown in the Electron through this box here, and you can refresh the PS counter with this button.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&quot;Thanks Bruce.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Sasha switched to Slide 1, marked Bill Nillt, and focused on one of the 'rocks'.  She smiled, &quot;Good횄짖창혗짭횂짝  these are about to reproduce횄짖창혗짭횂짝 or fracture.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&nbsp;</P>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Fred moved his attention to the man at the door; &quot;Can you get me a visual?&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The technician shrugged, &quot;The best I could do is to tap into the Hospital's security cameras횄짖창혗짭횂짝  It's against Colony Policy, however.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&quot;Do it횄짖창혗짭횂짝  I'll mend things later.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The technician shrugged again, &quot;Yes, sir, whatever you say.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&nbsp;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Sasha growled, &quot;Come on횄짖창혗짭횂짝 almost there횄짖창혗짭횂짝  ah횄짖창혗짭횂짝  they have split횄짖창혗짭횂짝  Good.&quot;</P>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&quot;Why is that good?&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Sasha sighed, &quot;Now I can watch one grow.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Sasha began narrating once more; &quot;Okay횄짖창혗짭횂짝  so far nothing has happened with one of the newly created 'rocks'.  The thing has started to gain mass횄짖창혗짭횂짝  the pock marks have started to oscillate slowly횄짖창혗짭횂짝  this thing is most definitely alive횄짖창혗짭횂짝  however it seems to be inorganic in appearance횄짖창혗짭횂짝  hmm횄짖창혗짭횂짝&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&quot;Silicon-based life?&quot; suggested Bruce.</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Sasha shrugged, &quot;Its possible, but it is unlikely, as the conditions necessary to form and support Silicon-based life are very rare횄짖창혗짭횂짝  but it may be akin to it.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Bruce asked aloud, &quot;So what do we do to fend of something our scanners and antibodies don't recognize as alien?&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Fred chuckled over the intercom, &quot;We figure out why first.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&nbsp;</P>
