</B></FONT><I><FONT FACE="Tahoma"><P ALIGN="CENTER">&quot;The ability to respond to stimuli in the environment is an important characteristic of living things횄짖창혗짭횂짝 many of the structures and behaviors that you see enable them to respond to stimuli횄짖창혗짭횂짝&quot;</P>
</I></FONT><FONT FACE="Futurist"><P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P></DIR>
</DIR>
</DIR>
</DIR>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Fred sighed; it was going to be a long night. &quot;Sasha, stay at that end, and watch the patients횄짖창혗짭횂짝  we just received our batch of blood samples and will begin testing them.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">He walked back into the main room of the Laboratory facilities.  &quot;Okay people, this is why we are all here, lets get cracking on finding the solution to our first major problem: what does the body think that this virus is, and how do we subjugate that?&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The room became busy with activity횄짖창혗짭횂짝  trial and error using different substances to &quot;coat&quot; the &quot;rocks&quot; with some disguising chemical by changing the texture or color or look or feel.  A call rang out from one corner.</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&quot;Yes, Assistant Drieflusst?&quot; replied Fred.</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">&quot;Dr. Garcia, the virus is shrugging of these colored dyes.&quot;</P>
<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></P>

<P ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Fred walked to the terminal where the Assistant was situated; &quot;Could it be that the coloring is what makes the antibodies ignore it?&quot;</P>
